aa(lp72
VSo the ancient Greeks knew
p73
aVthat dogs sent invisible signals between each other.
p74
aVA female dog in heat
p75
aVsent an invisible signal to male dogs
p76
aVfor miles around,
p77
aVand it wasn't a sound, it was a smell.
p78
aVYou could take the smell from the female dog,
p79
aVand the dogs would chase the cloth.
p80
aVBut the problem for everybody
p81
aVwho could see this effect
p82
aVwas that you couldn't identify the molecules.
p83
aVYou couldn't demonstrate it was chemical.
p84
aVThe reason for that, of course,
p85
aVis that each of these animals
p86
aVproduces tiny quantities,
p87
aVand in the case of the dog,
p88
aVmales dogs can smell it, but we can't smell it.
p89
aVAnd it was only in 1959 that a German team,
p90
aVafter spending 20 years in search of these molecules,
p91
aVdiscovered, identified, the first pheromone,
p92
aVand this was the sex pheromone of a silk moth.
p93
aVNow, this was an inspired choice  by Adolf Butenandt and his team,
p94
aVbecause he needed half a million moths
p95
aVto get enough material to do the chemical analysis.
p96
aVBut he created the model
p97
aVfor how you should go about pheromone analysis.
p98
aVHe basically went through systematically,
p99
aVshowing that only the molecule in question
p100
aVwas the one that stimulated the males,
p101
aVnot all the others.
p102
aVHe analyzed it very carefully.
p103
aVHe synthesized the molecule,
p104
aVand then tried the synthesized molecule on the males
p105
aVand got them to respond and showed it was,
p106
aVindeed, that molecule.
p107
aVThat's closing the circle.
p108
aVThat's the thing which has never been done with humans:
p109
aVnothing systematic, no real demonstration.
p110
aa(lp111
VWith that new concept,
p112
aVwe needed a new word,
p113
aVand that was the word "pheromone,"
p114
aVand it's basically transferred excitement,
p115
aVtransferred between individuals,
p116
aVand since 1959, pheromones have been found
p117
aVright the way across the animal kingdom,
p118
aVin male animals, in female animals.
p119
aVIt works just as well underwater
p120
aVfor goldfish and lobsters.
